Sexual Freedom is the third film of the Sex Stories trilogy. Honestly, it's a risque film, but that does not take away from the beauty of the journey Olvidie takes to find himself sexually, and discover that 'free love' is a lot more than he realized. I was pleasantly surprised at how much a enjoyed watching this film, and would certainly recommend this film to anyone who is considering it!

Ovidie makes wonderful films. In this film, she films a group of young people on location, living in a commune. There is explicit sex, where everyone switches around.  Ovidie interviews the participants, and films their activities. The best scene is the last scene (not at the commune)  where a 25 year old girl has married a 65 year old fat guy, who has won the lottery. The girl has sex with a younger man, so her old husband can watch. The old guy keeps dozing off. In the end, Ovidie is disgusted about what she's doing, and wants to try another kind of career. Very funny scene. In all, a good film.
